# Drizzle ORM Documentation

Use current Drizzle docs — do not rely on training data for API details.

## Priority 1: Drizzle MCP server

If the `drizzle` MCP server is available, use these tools:

1. `search_drizzle_docs` — search indexed topics from `orm.drizzle.team/llms.txt`
2. `fetch_drizzle_doc` — fetch page content by slug (e.g. `overview`, `drizzle-config-file`)
3. `list_drizzle_topics` — list all indexed topics, optionally filtered by section

Workflow: search first, then fetch the most relevant page.

## Priority 2: Context7 MCP (fallback)

If Drizzle MCP servers are unavailable, use Context7 `resolve-library-id` then `query-docs`:

| Topic | Preferred Context7 library ID |
| --- | --- |
| Drizzle ORM (docs) | `/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs` |
| Drizzle ORM (source) | `/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm` |
| LLMs index | `/llmstxt/orm_drizzle_team_llms_txt` |
| Docs website | `/websites/orm_drizzle_team` |

Pass the user's full question as the `query` parameter.

## Priority 3: Direct sources (shell fallback)

```bash
# Browse the full doc index
curl -s https://orm.drizzle.team/llms.txt

# Fetch source markdown from GitHub
curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/main/src/content/docs/overview.mdx
curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/main/src/content/docs/drizzle-config-file.mdx
curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/main/src/content/docs/pg/kit-overview.mdx
```

